HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 938
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to recognize Steve Gaston on the occasion of
his retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that the members of this General Assembly should honor
those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their
years of public service; and
WHEREAS, Steve Gaston of Hamilton County is one such estimable person, who
evinces the greatest integrity and probity in all his chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, after thirty-two years of distinguished service to the Hamilton County
Election Commission, Mr. Gaston is taking a much-deserved retirement; and
WHEREAS, Steve Gaston exemplifies the spirit and allegiance to family and community
that are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Gaston is wholly committed to the noble precepts of public service that
have earned Tennessee recognition as the Volunteer State, and he should be specially
recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we commend Steve Gaston for his honorable and astute service to the
Hamilton County Election Commission, extending to him our heartfelt wishes for a happy and
fulfilling retirement and every continued success in his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
